class_name SystemDB
extends RefCounted
# The STAR CATALOGUE you travel. Each system is its own LOCAL, small-coordinate arena
# (1 unit = 0.1 AU) — you NEVER fly the real interstellar distance, so float precision is
# never stressed. The real light-year distance + sky coordinates are display/transit/
# map metadata only.
#
# Two data sources, unified by id (see _rows):
#   • STARS    — ~45 REAL nearest stars (generated by tools/gen_star_catalog.py from the
#                J2000 nearest-star table). Each is a single tinted sol.obj star.
#   • AUTHORED — the hand-built systems with custom planet/live/hostile layouts (Sol live,
#                Proxima b, TRAPPIST-1, K2-18, the imaginary Alien zone).
#
# A "body spec" is what PlanetSystem.load_system() consumes:
#   name, radius (visual), color, glow, model (opt GLB/OBJ), star (bool),
#   live (bool — Sol's Sun/planets read live positions from Ephemeris),
#   pos  (Vector3 local scene units — used when live == false).

